  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Using Octopress on Fedora 20]]></title>
    <link href="http://kwierman.github.io/blog/2015/01/24/using-octopress-on-fedora-20/"/>
    <updated>2015-01-24T15:36:07-05:00</updated>
    <id>http://kwierman.github.io/blog/2015/01/24/using-octopress-on-fedora-20</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In order to get the code blocks working the way I wanted them to, </p>

<pre lang="python"><code>def something:
  something else
end
</code></pre>

<p>The syntax for adding code in is:</p>

<pre lang="markdown"><code>```
  ``` [language] [title] [url] [link text]
  code snippet
  ```
```
</code></pre>

<p>So, for example, if you were to document a ruby code snippet:</p>

<div class="bogus-wrapper"><notextile><figure class="code"><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span>
<span class="line-number">2</span>
<span class="line-number">3</span>
</pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class=""><span class="line">``` html An html code snippet www.google.com And a link to google.com
</span><span class="line">&lt;div&gt; Some html-y stuff&lt;/div&gt;
</span><span class="line">```</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div>

<p>Would render to
&lt;div class=&#8217;bogus-wrapper&#8217;&gt;<notextile><figure class="code">&lt;figcaption&gt;<span>An html code snippet www.google.com And a link to google.com</span>&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;div class=&#8221;highlight&#8221;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#8221;gutter&#8221;&gt;&lt;pre class=&#8221;line-numbers&#8221;&gt;<span class="line-number">1</span>
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#8217;code&#8217;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;<code class="html"><span class="line"><span class="nt">&lt;div&gt;</span> Some html-y stuff<span class="nt">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
</span></code>&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</figure></notextile>&lt;/div&gt;</p>

<p>These instructions can be found at: <a href="http://octopress.org/docs/blogging/code/">The Octopress Site</a>.
What they lack is telling you that single backticks can be used for inline code blocking.</p>

<p>In addition, the following was added to the source/_includes/header for LATEX support:
&lt;div class=&#8217;bogus-wrapper&#8217;&gt;<notextile><figure class="code">&lt;figcaption&gt;<span>An html code snippet www.google.com And a link to google.com</span>&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;div class=&#8221;highlight&#8221;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#8221;gutter&#8221;&gt;&lt;pre class=&#8221;line-numbers&#8221;&gt;<span class="line-number">1</span>
<span class="line-number">2</span>
<span class="line-number">3</span>
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#8217;code&#8217;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;<code class="html"><span class="line"><span class="nt">&lt;script </span><span class="na">type=</span><span class="s">&quot;text/javascript&quot;</span>
</span><span class="line">        <span class="na">src=</span><span class="s">&quot;http://cdn.mathjax.org/mathjax/latest/MathJax.js?config=TeX-AMS-MML_HTMLorMML&quot;</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
</span><span class="line"><span class="nt">&lt;/script&gt;</span>
</span></code>&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</figure></notextile>&lt;/div&gt;</p>

<p>This now allows us to things like <script type="math/tex"> \frac{\Delta x}{\Delta p} \ge \frac{\hbar}{2}</script></p>

<p>This was done thank you to: <a href="http://kqueue.org/blog/2012/01/05/hello-world/#internal-post-linking"> Another Octopress blog</a>.</p>

]]></content>
